The article is a Presidential Memorandum from February 25, 2015, titled "Establishment of the Cyber Threat Intelligence Integration Center." The memorandum directs the Director of National Intelligence (DNI) to establish a Cyber Threat Intelligence Integration Center (CTIIC) and outlines its responsibilities. The CTIIC is tasked with providing integrated all-source analysis of intelligence related to foreign cyber threats or incidents affecting U.S. national interests. It will support various government entities involved in cybersecurity and intelligence activities and oversee the development of intelligence sharing capabilities. The CTIIC will also ensure the dissemination of threat reporting to both government and private sector entities and support interagency efforts to counter foreign cyber threats. The memorandum emphasizes the need to protect privacy and civil liberties in the implementation of these initiatives. The DNI is authorized and directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.